results.wikipedia_summary: Eurystomus is a genus of roller, one of the two genera in that family of birds. It contains four broad-billed species, which breed in Africa, Asia and Australasia. Two species are restricted to Africa, one of which, the Cinnamon Roller, is migratory. The Dollarbird has a large distribution ranging from India to Japan and Australia. It too is migratory over the northern and southern extremes of its range. The final species, the Azure Roller, is endemic...
